article.headline: Western Kentucky 83, Austin Peay 54
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Benson Callier scored 21 points to lead Western Kentucky to a season-opening 83-54 victory over Austin Peay Friday night. Callier, a junior transfer from Florida State, was 8-of-12 from the floor, including his first four attempts from beyond the 3-point line. Ty Rogers added 13 points for Western, while Boris Siakam finished with 12. Zac Schlader led Austin Peay with 12 points. Todd Babington added 11. The Hilltoppers never trailed and took control of the game with an early 14-0 run that gave them a 25-7 lead with 10:24 to play in the first half. They led by as many 30 points several times late in the game. Western Kentucky finished 18-of-34 (52.9 percent) from the floor in the first half and 35-of-71 (49.2 percent) for the game. Austin Peay struggled from the floor, shooting just 7-of-21 (33.3 percent) in the first half and 18-of-51 (35.2 percent) for the game.
